## 1. Platform Intellectual Property

### 1.1 SpiriVerse Brand and Trademarks

All trademarks, service marks, trade names, logos, and brand identifiers associated with SpiriVerse, including but not limited to the "SpiriVerse" name, logo, taglines, and visual identity (collectively, "SpiriVerse Marks"), are the exclusive property of [COMPANY_ENTITY]. These marks are protected under applicable trademark laws in Australia, the United Kingdom, the United States, and internationally.

No User may use, reproduce, modify, or display any SpiriVerse Marks without prior written authorization from [COMPANY_ENTITY]. Unauthorized use of SpiriVerse Marks may constitute trademark infringement and will be pursued to the fullest extent permitted by law.

### 1.2 Platform Software and Technology

The Platform's software, source code, algorithms, databases, architecture, user interfaces, and all related technical infrastructure are the proprietary property of [COMPANY_ENTITY] and are protected by copyright, trade secret, and other intellectual property laws. Users are strictly prohibited from:

- Reverse engineering, decompiling, or disassembling any portion of the Platform;
- Copying, reproducing, or creating derivative works based on Platform software or design;
- Scraping, crawling, or extracting data from the Platform through automated means without written permission;
- Circumventing any technological protection measures implemented on the Platform.

### 1.3 Platform Design and Content

The overall look and feel of the Platform, including its layout, design elements, color schemes, typography, icons, graphics, and editorial content produced by SpiriVerse, are protected by copyright and other intellectual property rights. These elements remain the exclusive property of [COMPANY_ENTITY].

---

## 2. User-Generated Content Ownership

### 2.1 Retention of Ownership

Users retain full ownership of all original content they create and upload to the Platform ("User Content"). This includes, but is not limited to:

- Community posts, comments, reviews, and discussion contributions;
- Profile information, biographies, and avatar images;
- Ratings, testimonials, and feedback;
- Any other content submitted by Users in the course of using the Platform.

### 2.2 Representations and Warranties

By uploading or submitting User Content to the Platform, you represent and warrant that:

- You are the original creator or have obtained all necessary rights, licenses, and permissions to use and share the content;
- The content does not infringe, misappropriate, or violate the intellectual property rights, privacy rights, or any other rights of any third party;
- The content complies with all applicable laws and regulations in the jurisdictions where it is made available;
- You have obtained all necessary consents from any individuals depicted, referenced, or otherwise identifiable in the content.

### 2.3 Responsibility for User Content

Users are solely responsible for the content they upload, publish, or otherwise make available on the Platform. SpiriVerse does not endorse, verify, or assume liability for any User Content.

---

## 3. Merchant Content

### 3.1 Product Listings and Descriptions

Vendors who sell products on the Platform ("Merchants") retain ownership of all original content created for their storefronts, including but not limited to:

- Product listings, titles, and descriptions;
- Original product photography and images;
- Custom oracle and tarot deck designs, card artwork, and accompanying guidebooks;
- Handmade jewelry designs and related imagery;
- Original artwork, prints, and digital art;
- Books, e-books, and written publications;
- Packaging designs and product presentation materials.

### 3.2 Storefront Branding

Merchants retain ownership of their custom storefront branding, including:

- Business logos and wordmarks;
- Banner images and storefront graphics;
- Brand descriptions, taglines, and "About" content;
- Custom color schemes and visual presentations created by the Merchant.

### 3.3 Merchant Obligations

Merchants are responsible for ensuring that all content uploaded to their storefronts is original or properly licensed. Merchants must not:

- Use images, descriptions, or designs obtained from other sellers, artists, or creators without authorization;
- Reproduce or replicate copyrighted card designs, artwork, or branding belonging to third parties;
- Misrepresent the origin, authorship, or authenticity of any product or product-related content.

---

## 4. Practitioner Content

### 4.1 Ownership of Practitioner Works

Practitioners who offer services and content on the Platform retain ownership of their original works, including but not limited to:

- Written readings, interpretations, and spiritual consultations;
- Voice recordings, audio readings, and oracle messages;
- Guided meditations and visualization recordings;
- Original curriculum for events, workshops, and courses;
- Livestream content and presentations;
- On-demand video content, podcasts, and recorded lectures;
- Course materials, handouts, workbooks, and supplementary resources;
- Teaching methodologies and original spiritual frameworks.

### 4.2 Practitioner Obligations

Practitioners are responsible for ensuring that all content they offer through the Platform is original or appropriately licensed. Practitioners must:

- Create original content based on their own knowledge, experience, and expertise;
- Properly attribute and obtain permission for any third-party content incorporated into their offerings;
- Respect the intellectual property of other practitioners, authors, and content creators;
- Not reproduce, recite, or distribute copyrighted works (such as published books, card deck guidebooks, or proprietary teachings) without authorization from the rights holder.

---

